Two girls from the same family on Monday died after the red soil quarry in which they were digging caved in.The two girls aged nine and 13 years from Monyerero village, Kisii county, were digging the soil to decorate their house when the quarry collapsed at 1pm.County police commander Agnes Mudamba said they were pulled out at 3pm and rushed to Christamariane Hospital. They were dead on arrival. &ldquo;Police rushed to the scene to assist in the rescue, but they found that the villagers had retrieved the girls and rushed them to hospital,&rdquo; she said. Mudamba urged parents not to send their children to dig soil, especially during the rainy seasons.